
[1]impunity

   IMPU'NITY, n. [L. impunitas; in and punio, to punish.]

   1. Exemption from punishment or penalty. No person should be permitted
   to violate the laws with impunity. Impunity encourages men in crimes.

   2. Freedom or exemption from injury. Some ferocious animals are not be
   encountered with impunity.
